.TH F00-RM 1 "2026" "f00 0.15.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
f00\-rm \- remove files or directories (f00tils)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B f00\-rm
[\fIOPTION\fR]... \fIFILE\fR...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Remove (unlink) the FILE(s). Pure assembly multicall. MIT.
.PP
Default is modern mode.
.B \-\-core
selects strict GNU rm\-compatible behavior.
.SH COREUTILS FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-force\fR
ignore nonexistent files and arguments, never prompt
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-R\fR, \fB\-\-recursive\fR
remove directories and their contents recursively
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
explain what is being done
.TP
\fB\-i\fR
prompt before every removal
.PP
See
.B f00\-rm \-\-help
for the full flag list.
.SH MODERN FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-\-core\fR
strict coreutils\-compatible mode
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR
JSON summary when supported
.TP
\fB\-\-csv\fR
CSV summary when supported
.SH AUTHOR
f00 contributors. License MIT.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rm (1),
.BR f00\-rmdir (1),
.BR f00 (1)
.PP
https://f00.sh
